Improve article clustering to group semantically similar articles

Fix issue where articles about the same topic (e.g., Iranian hackers targeting
critical infrastructure) were not being clustered together.

Changes:
- Lower semantic similarity threshold from 0.8 to 0.65 in optimization.py
  (more aggressive clustering for cybersecurity articles)
- Improve AI deduplication prompt to use title + analysis snippets instead of
  just titles, enabling better semantic understanding
- Simplify frontend dedup to preserve backend topic clustering while removing
  exact duplicates (first 80 chars match)
- Add AI verification for uncertain similarity cases (0.45-0.65 range)

Tested with Iranian hacker articles from BleepingComputer and DataBreaches.net
- Now correctly clustered together (semantic similarity > 0.65)
- Unrelated articles correctly kept separate

